From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 15:38:44 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/7] Fix timezone bug in market-hours guard and a crash in
 Telegram notifications

The pipeline reached full APPROVED -> Risk-approved -> Execution for the
first time this session (GOLD, 15:34:05 UTC), surfacing two real bugs at
the last step before a fill:

- safety/guard.py: TradingGuard.check_session/check_holiday/check_market_closing
  computed "current time" via datetime.now(timezone.utc).astimezone() with no
  explicit timezone, which resolves to the server/container's local timezone
  (UTC in this environment) rather than India Standard Time. NSE market hours
  (09:15-15:30) are always IST, so on a UTC server every check was comparing
  the wrong clock entirely - it happened to spuriously block this order because
  15:34 UTC coincidentally falls in the 09:15-15:30 window as a naive string,
  even though real IST time was 21:04 (correctly after-hours, but for the wrong
  reason). Fixed by explicitly converting to ZoneInfo("Asia/Kolkata").
- telegram/bot.py: send_message() called logger.debug(msg, msg=message) - the
  msg= keyword collided with the positional `msg` parameter StructuredLogger.debug()
  already binds, raising "got multiple values for argument 'msg'" and crashing
  the TelegramNotifier agent's execution_failed handler.

Added regression tests: one verifies TradingGuard.check_session's decision
matches independently-computed IST time (fails on a UTC server without the
fix), the other reproduces the exact send_message() crash with no credentials
configured.

Note: with the timezone fix, real IST time is currently after NSE market hours
(21:04 IST), so the session guard now correctly blocks new orders until the
next real market open - this is expected behavior for a guard modeling real
exchange hours, not a bug.

